Knock wood but I am completely ‘unscathed.’  Kinda amazing!

I guess that wasn't a surprise tho. This stuff kills you and it's even legal. Give them some weed (kidding!)
This was interesting. If he didn't get rid of the excess fluid, I also wonder what happened to his kidneys. The liver would probably not have a good time either but that is individual.

I guess this also might explain a common hangover, at least if we assume alcohol is diuretic. So even if you eat it might not be enough I take of minerals and proteins on a night out, and you get the famous hangover, against witch is no cure till this day.
So if my guess is right, and ethanol in itself is diuretic, it would make a difference in the exchange of important minerals like sodium and potassium? Even in much smaller amounts than 15 liters of beer a day 😉
